      <div type="transcription" xml:id="transcription_aad_0099" xml:lang="en">
        <div type="letter">
        <pb facs="https://iiif.acdh.oeaw.ac.at/aad/aad_00327/" ed="1r" type="sheet"/>
          <div>
            <ab hand="#hand_gray_onb">
              <lb/>15<unclear>|</unclear>B870<unclear>|</unclear>2
            </ab>
          </div>
          <div type="letter_message" hand="#type_cc_spiel">
            <opener>
              <dateline>
                <lb/><space quantity="29" unit="char"/>xxx 06138/515
                <date>
                  <lb/><space quantity="26" unit="char"/>1st July 1972
                </date>
              </dateline>
              <salute>
                <lb/>Dear <rs type="person" ref="#amp_person_1">Mr Auden</rs>,
              </salute>
            </opener>
            <p>
              <lb/><space quantity="5" unit="char"/><rs type="lit_work" ref="#lit_work_id_99">Your statement</rs> which <rs type="person" ref="#amp_person_78">I</rs> will duly trans-
              <lb/>late seems to indicate that your case is being
              <lb/>conducted with utter id<add place="inline" hand="#type_cc_spiel">i</add>ocy. I am sure something
              <lb/>can be done to avert a court case and a lot
              <lb/>of highly unpleasan<subst><del rend="overtyped" hand="#type_cc_spiel">g</del><add place="superimposed" hand="#type_cc_spiel">t</add></subst> publicity for the Austrian
              <lb/>authorities. I should like to write to <rs type="person" ref="#amp_person_282">Dr.Kreis-
              <lb/>ky</rs> and to show him <rs type="lit_work" ref="#lit_work_id_105">your statement</rs>, if you
              <lb/>agree. However, I would like to ask you whether
              <lb/>you could not - for this very reason - s<subst><del rend="overtyped" hand="#type_cc_spiel">hlit<unclear>h</unclear>y</del><add place="superimposed" hand="#type_cc_spiel">lightl</add></subst>y
              <lb/>alter t<subst><del rend="overtyped" hand="#type_cc_spiel">z</del><add place="superimposed" hand="#type_cc_spiel">h</add></subst>e last words of <rs type="lit_work" ref="#lit_work_id_99">your statem<subst><del rend="overtyped" hand="#type_cc_spiel">t</del><add place="superimposed" hand="#type_cc_spiel">e</add></subst>nt</rs>.
              <lb/>I feel, in all humility, that it would be
              <lb/>more impressive and less offensive to say
              <lb/>something like 'let me warn you that this
              <lb/>would cause a world scandal'. I should feel
              <lb/>happier if you would agree to this, in view
              <lb/>of my plan to involve <rs type="person" ref="#amp_person_282">Dr.Kreisky</rs> in the <rs type="event" ref="#amp_event_id_45">affair</rs><unclear><subst><del rend="overtyped" hand="#type_cc_spiel">-</del><add place="superimposed" hand="#type_cc_spiel">.</add></subst></unclear>
            </p>
            <closer>
              <salute>
                <lb/><space quantity="22" unit="char"/>Yours sincerely,
              </salute>
            </closer>
          </div>
        <pb facs="https://iiif.acdh.oeaw.ac.at/aad/aad_00328/" ed="1v" type="sheet"/>
        </div>
      </div>
    </body>
